739
00:49:38,696 --> 00:49:42,450
I often come to the arena
not knowing whether I will practice.

740
00:49:42,616 --> 00:49:44,413
A couple of meetings -

741
00:49:44,576 --> 00:49:47,488
and then I go home,
eat and take a nap.

742
00:49:47,736 --> 00:49:50,330
Sirpa has made pasta
on game days for 20 years.

743
00:49:50,496 --> 00:49:54,011
Always quite the same.

744
00:49:54,176 --> 00:49:58,294
It has always been...
- Good? - Yes.

745
00:49:58,456 --> 00:50:00,765
He has a professional attitude -

746
00:50:00,936 --> 00:50:03,769
towards training
and preparation.

747
00:50:03,936 --> 00:50:08,088
I followed him as a young boy
and tried to learn from him.

748
00:50:08,376 --> 00:50:13,689
There is pressure to win
and a fear of losing.

749
00:50:13,896 --> 00:50:18,447
I'm aware of it
but I do not think about it much.

750
00:50:18,616 --> 00:50:24,691
A typical thing for top athletes
is their tolerance for stress.

751
00:50:24,856 --> 00:50:27,416
Some don't even know what stress is.

752
00:50:27,576 --> 00:50:29,214
They are very laid back.

753
00:50:29,456 --> 00:50:34,211
The guy is always smiling,
but he still is a warrior.

754
00:50:34,376 --> 00:50:36,173
Physically and mentally.

755
00:50:36,336 --> 00:50:38,213
He wants to win and score goals.

756
00:50:38,376 --> 00:50:42,449
He is a dangerous player
because he is so fast -

757
00:50:42,616 --> 00:50:44,493
and can scores from bad positions.

758
00:50:44,776 --> 00:50:48,610
He makes very ugly goals -

759
00:50:49,296 --> 00:50:51,764
tip-ins and rebound goals.

760
00:50:51,976 --> 00:50:58,165
I have always had a sidekick
and then a third link in the chain.

761
00:50:58,336 --> 00:51:01,931
Right now I have none of them.

762
00:51:02,096 --> 00:51:06,567
When he's on his game, I play him a lot,
'cause I know good things are gonna happen.

763
00:51:06,976 --> 00:51:13,245
If you don't need ice packs
after the game -

764
00:51:13,416 --> 00:51:15,213
you haven't played hard enough.

765
00:51:15,896 --> 00:51:17,773
When I get up in the morning -

766
00:51:17,936 --> 00:51:20,814
I take my first steps
gently -

767
00:51:20,976 --> 00:51:22,807
to see where it hurts.

768
00:51:25,096 --> 00:51:29,533
It's challenging to recover quickly
after a game.

769
00:51:29,696 --> 00:51:33,928
I stretch
10-15 minutes every night.

770
00:51:34,096 --> 00:51:36,166
We also have
cold and hot baths.

771
00:51:36,336 --> 00:51:38,611
Two minutes in both -

772
00:51:38,776 --> 00:51:42,530
maybe four times,
so I get lactic acid moving.

773
00:51:42,696 --> 00:51:45,654
Careers are longer nowadays -

774
00:51:45,856 --> 00:51:49,451
because medicine
and especially treating injuries  -

775
00:51:49,616 --> 00:51:51,607
have evolved greatly.

776
00:51:52,576 --> 00:51:57,013
This year, I have noticed that if we have
games two days in a row -

777
00:51:57,216 --> 00:52:01,414
I don't have full energy
in the second game.

778
00:52:02,496 --> 00:52:05,169
I guess my age is starting to show.

779
00:52:07,016 --> 00:52:09,007
We were away for 13 days -

780
00:52:09,176 --> 00:52:12,566
and for some reason
I slept poorly all the time.

781
00:52:12,736 --> 00:52:15,967
A few times I thought
that this probably is my last year.

782
00:52:16,136 --> 00:52:21,130
But after a few days of rest
and a good game -

783
00:52:21,296 --> 00:52:25,369
you change your mind.
I realized this is pretty fun.

784
00:52:25,696 --> 00:52:31,532
He won't probably stop playing
hockey until a doctor forbids him.

785
00:52:31,696 --> 00:52:35,609
When we played 26 games in 44 days -

786
00:52:36,456 --> 00:52:41,132
there were nights when I wasn't recovered.

787
00:52:41,376 --> 00:52:44,766
I am grateful that my old
body did not give up.

788
00:52:47,776 --> 00:52:50,370
I like to listen to Finnish music.

789
00:52:50,536 --> 00:52:52,766
I do not know if I'm homesick -

790
00:52:53,216 --> 00:52:57,687
but especially abroad
and on game trips -

791
00:52:57,856 --> 00:53:01,451
music has a special significance.

792
00:53:01,736 --> 00:53:04,694
When I'm driving home late at night
-

793
00:53:04,936 --> 00:53:07,575
listening to Arttu Wiskari
makes me feel good.

794
00:53:09,696 --> 00:53:16,568
<i> It was June 1986, </ i>
<i> our Sierra was almost new </ i>

795
00:53:17,136 --> 00:53:22,051
<i> Dad filled up, </ i>
<i> mom packed lunch < / i>

796
00:53:24,576 --> 00:53:32,005
<i> I was already sitting in the back seat, </ i>
<i> I smiled broadly with the seat belt on </ i>

797
00:53:32,176 --> 00:53:37,045
<i> Dingo sang about the girl in the leather jacket </ i>

798
00:53:40,096 --> 00:53:42,007
My brother Paavo called me.

799
00:53:42,176 --> 00:53:46,294
My father had suffered a stroke.
Fortunately, a fairly mild.

800
00:53:47,016 --> 00:53:52,932
He lost feeling in his hand
and his posture was crooked.

801
00:53:53,096 --> 00:53:55,007
His eyelids drooped.

802
00:53:55,576 --> 00:53:58,568
Such news make you stop and think
to stay up -

803
00:53:58,736 --> 00:54:01,534
especially when you live
far from Finland -

804
00:54:01,896 --> 00:54:03,932
and your loved ones.

805
00:54:12,176 --> 00:54:15,168
We fly often in
really bad weather -

806
00:54:15,336 --> 00:54:18,772
because we have a
game the next day.

807
00:54:18,976 --> 00:54:23,367
It's idiotic.
It scares me the most.

808
00:54:23,536 --> 00:54:27,927
What happened last year -

809
00:54:28,096 --> 00:54:32,009
has always been my biggest nightmare.

810
00:54:32,176 --> 00:54:35,771
When the plane crashed in Yaroslavl -

811
00:54:36,216 --> 00:54:40,926
I felt that this is not
worth playing anymore.

812
00:54:42,776 --> 00:54:45,131
I lost  many old teammates.

813
00:54:45,336 --> 00:54:48,851
Ruslan Salej
was a really good friend of mine.

814
00:54:49,016 --> 00:54:52,053
I played with Igor
Korolev in Winnipeg.

815
00:54:52,216 --> 00:54:55,208
And Karpovtsev...
They were unbelievable guys.

816
00:55:11,856 --> 00:55:19,012
I sharpened Teemu's skates
until he turned 12.

817
00:55:20,416 --> 00:55:24,170
Most players don't know a thing about
skate sharpening and curvatures.

818
00:55:24,416 --> 00:55:27,852
We were lucky enough
to get to try different versions -

819
00:55:28,016 --> 00:55:29,813
and find the best one.

820
00:55:30,496 --> 00:55:34,489
We tried many different options.

821
00:55:34,736 --> 00:55:37,808
Many said that I sharpened them wrong.

822
00:55:38,016 --> 00:55:40,291
They said that the grooves were too deep.

823
00:55:40,456 --> 00:55:42,731
That human ankles can't handle it.

824
00:55:43,456 --> 00:55:47,085
I was the doorman at the pub
Kosmos for 30 years.

825
00:55:47,256 --> 00:55:49,087
Near the end of the second period -

826
00:55:49,256 --> 00:55:52,214
I got a phone call from Ismo
Syvähuoko, the Jokerit doctor.

827
00:55:52,376 --> 00:55:55,174
He said Teemu's skates need
to be sharpened.

828
00:55:55,336 --> 00:55:58,931
I called a taxi
and went to the arena.

829
00:55:59,096 --> 00:56:02,486
I went to the grinding room
in my suit.

830
00:56:02,696 --> 00:56:04,448
I sharpened his skates, -

831
00:56:04,616 --> 00:56:07,176
jumped into a taxi
and went back to work.

832
00:56:07,696 --> 00:56:11,052
He sharpened 10 blades for me
before every NHL season.

833
00:56:11,456 --> 00:56:16,928
We followed what he had done in Finland
and just tried to emulate that.

834
00:56:17,176 --> 00:56:19,007
We developed a padding -

835
00:56:19,176 --> 00:56:22,964
which was between the glove
and the elbow pad -

836
00:56:23,136 --> 00:56:25,252
to protect his arms.

837
00:56:26,016 --> 00:56:28,052
The ice is better in Finland -

838
00:56:29,136 --> 00:56:33,812
and I used to play
with this narrower blade.

839
00:56:34,096 --> 00:56:37,133
The ice in the NHL is really bad.

840
00:56:37,696 --> 00:56:43,373
It turns to slush
after five minutes of play.

841
00:56:43,936 --> 00:56:46,496
It was annoying
to get a good pass -

842
00:56:46,656 --> 00:56:48,806
that bounced over the blade.

843
00:56:48,976 --> 00:56:51,046
This makes the stick a little heavier.

844
00:56:51,216 --> 00:56:54,891
It bothers many players,
but I don't mind.

845
00:56:55,456 --> 00:56:57,412
I can say with my hand on my heart -

846
00:56:57,576 --> 00:57:00,807
that I haven't heard about
any player who has doped -

847
00:57:00,976 --> 00:57:02,807
or even been offered any.

848
00:57:02,976 --> 00:57:05,968
A hockey player can fill himself
with drugs -

849
00:57:06,136 --> 00:57:08,331
but it takes so much more.

850
00:57:08,496 --> 00:57:13,092
You have to have hockey sense,
skill and technique.

851
00:57:13,296 --> 00:57:17,414
There are sports
that doping suit.

852
00:57:17,576 --> 00:57:20,613
Ice hockey is not one of them.

853
00:57:21,016 --> 00:57:26,044
All the Finnish top coaches
in individual sports -

854
00:57:26,216 --> 00:57:29,492
like Kari-Pekka Kyro,
are convinced -

855
00:57:29,656 --> 00:57:32,853
that most NHL players
use illegal drugs.

856
00:57:33,056 --> 00:57:36,765
Ice hockey is the world's toughest sport.

857
00:57:37,536 --> 00:57:40,767
They have skates and a stick -

858
00:57:40,976 --> 00:57:42,853
A small puck and they play on ice.

859
00:57:43,016 --> 00:57:44,529
If the alternative is -

860
00:57:44,696 --> 00:57:48,086
earning $ 1,500 a month
in the East Coast Hockey League -

861
00:57:48,256 --> 00:57:49,928
or a million a year in the NHL -

862
00:57:50,096 --> 00:57:52,291
you'd do anything
to play in the NHL.

863
00:57:52,456 --> 00:57:55,573
You can't be on drugs -

864
00:57:55,816 --> 00:57:58,569
if you want to move fast
in a small area.

865
00:57:59,016 --> 00:58:04,215
Since doping is forbidden,

866
00:58:04,776 --> 00:58:06,767
if we want to get rid of the problem -

867
00:58:06,936 --> 00:58:10,531
cheaters must be banned
for life right away.

868
00:58:10,696 --> 00:58:12,891
1991 WORLD
CHAMPIONSHIPS

869
00:58:15,936 --> 00:58:17,574
<i> Selanne shoots! </ i>

870
00:58:19,056 --> 00:58:25,894
When I was a small boy
I wanted to play in SM-liiga.

871
00:58:26,536 --> 00:58:29,209
My dream was
to be in the national team.

872
00:58:29,976 --> 00:58:37,052
My fantasy, which felt distant
and even unrealistic -

873
00:58:37,216 --> 00:58:40,014
was to get to the NHL.

874
00:58:43,296 --> 00:58:46,845
I played in a 4 country tournament
in Seinäjoki when I was 16.

875
00:58:47,176 --> 00:58:49,406
When I got the national team jersey -

876
00:58:49,576 --> 00:58:53,251
I shuddered because I had
dreamed about it for so long.

877
00:58:53,416 --> 00:58:59,605
The national team has helped me
step into bigger boots.

878
00:59:00,336 --> 00:59:02,930
<i> Teemu scores! </ i>

879
00:59:03,296 --> 00:59:06,527
The Nagano Olympics
were an incredible experience.

880
00:59:06,696 --> 00:59:10,974
For the first time
the best players from the NHL -

881
00:59:11,136 --> 00:59:13,127
played in their national teams.

882
00:59:14,216 --> 00:59:16,093
<i> Two against one. </ I>

883
00:59:16,256 --> 00:59:19,566
<i> Koivu, Selanne. </ I>
<i> Selanne scores! </ i>

884
00:59:19,776 --> 00:59:22,688
The quarter final was the first
"do or die" game.

885
00:59:22,856 --> 00:59:25,495
Sweden had their <i> dream team. </ I>

886
00:59:25,656 --> 00:59:29,615
<i> Nice pass from Saku Koivu </ i>

887
00:59:30,856 --> 00:59:35,486
In the 1999 World Championships
the finals were a two game series.

888
00:59:36,616 --> 00:59:39,574
We lost the first
against the Czechs with one goal -

889
00:59:39,736 --> 00:59:42,204
won the second with three goals.

890
00:59:42,376 --> 00:59:46,528
I celebrated for a while
before I remembered the rules.

891
00:59:47,336 --> 00:59:51,454
The atmosphere was a bit flat
when we went into overtime.

892
00:59:52,136 --> 00:59:54,809
We lost in overtime.

893
00:59:56,456 --> 00:59:59,016
<i> So it goes. </ I>
<i> Nothing to do about it. </ I>

894
01:00:00,496 --> 01:00:06,048
In the 2006 Olympics -

895
01:00:06,576 --> 01:00:08,692
we were without a doubt the best team.

896
01:00:08,856 --> 01:00:12,087
All the pieces fell into place.

897
01:00:13,056 --> 01:00:15,286
Everyone found his role immediately.

898
01:00:17,376 --> 01:00:22,006
Too bad we lost in the final.

899
01:00:22,776 --> 01:00:24,732
<i> Sweden win Olympic gold! </ i>

900
01:00:24,896 --> 01:00:28,935
I would also have
wanted to win with the national team.

901
01:00:36,896 --> 01:00:41,094
My brother Panu and I
are both social.

902
01:00:42,736 --> 01:00:47,412
Panu needed money for drugs.

903
01:00:48,416 --> 01:00:52,295
We saw him sink really low.

904
01:00:52,496 --> 01:00:56,330
He was like a warning sign
for Paavo and me.

905
01:00:56,496 --> 01:00:58,293
We'll never go that route.

906
01:00:58,536 --> 01:01:01,209
I have often thought of -

907
01:01:01,376 --> 01:01:05,927
how much it was my fault -

908
01:01:06,136 --> 01:01:08,696
and what I could have
done differently.

909
01:01:08,856 --> 01:01:12,007
When Panu sat inside
in Sörnäinen Prison -

910
01:01:12,256 --> 01:01:15,692
he called me and asked for 500 Marks.

911
01:01:15,856 --> 01:01:18,848
"Come on Saturday
when it's visiting hours."

912
01:01:19,016 --> 01:01:24,966
We rolled up the money.

913
01:01:25,496 --> 01:01:30,251
Then we gave them to Panu
who hid them somewhere.

914
01:01:30,976 --> 01:01:36,528
He is my dear brother.
You try to help any way you can.

915
01:01:36,696 --> 01:01:38,891
Paavo has always
helped him a lot.

916
01:01:39,056 --> 01:01:41,047
And Mom, Dad and everyone else.

917
01:01:41,336 --> 01:01:45,124
I do know now
what I should have done.

918
01:01:45,296 --> 01:01:48,732
I should have spent more
time with my family.

919
01:01:50,296 --> 01:01:52,127
But it's good -

920
01:01:52,296 --> 01:01:57,893
That Panu has been clean
for over ten years.

921
01:01:58,056 --> 01:02:03,050
Paavo has been tougher
against Panu.

922
01:02:03,296 --> 01:02:05,605
He has said that we shouldn't
help him now.

923
01:02:05,896 --> 01:02:09,286
He has caused his own problems
and he must take the consequences.

924
01:02:10,016 --> 01:02:14,248
In my budget, I have counted
a moped a year to Panu -

925
01:02:15,176 --> 01:02:17,974
because he has absolutely
incredible stories.

926
01:02:18,136 --> 01:02:23,688
Panu is going to
visit for a month now.

927
01:02:24,176 --> 01:02:26,406
Panu!
- Hey!

928
01:02:27,736 --> 01:02:31,251
Leevi, how are you?
- My little darling.

929
01:02:31,976 --> 01:02:33,694
Good to see you.

930
01:02:33,856 --> 01:02:35,767
Teemu! How're you doing?

931
01:02:36,456 --> 01:02:38,606
Come here.
- Okay.

932
01:02:40,496 --> 01:02:43,329
Hey, what's your name?
- Daisy.

933
01:02:43,736 --> 01:02:46,125
Wow, that's a beautiful name.

934
01:02:46,456 --> 01:02:48,845
A friend gave me a book called -

935
01:02:49,256 --> 01:02:51,406
"How to choose
the sex of your child."

936
01:02:51,736 --> 01:02:55,206
Sirpa said that she wants a daughter.

937
01:02:55,376 --> 01:02:58,607
She was begging for two months.
I said, "Absolutely not."

938
01:02:58,776 --> 01:03:02,974
I begged for one month.
- It felt like two.

939
01:03:03,496 --> 01:03:08,365
Sirpa
read the book and then I looked through it.

940
01:03:08,656 --> 01:03:12,808
The book seemed logical.

941
01:03:13,176 --> 01:03:18,045
I wrote down a list of things
I would not have to do -

942
01:03:18,256 --> 01:03:19,894
and she signed it immediately.

943
01:03:21,136 --> 01:03:24,685
We started working on the project.

944
01:03:25,176 --> 01:03:28,213
If ovulation
was on a Wednesday -

945
01:03:28,816 --> 01:03:33,936
you would start early
if you wanted a girl.

946
01:03:34,376 --> 01:03:39,848
After 60 or 70 hours
all the boy sperms are gone.

947
01:03:40,416 --> 01:03:43,328
More than 90 percent are girls.

948
01:03:43,816 --> 01:03:45,852
We followed the instructions.

949
01:03:46,136 --> 01:03:50,812
It was great to hear the
gynecologist say it was a girl.

950
01:03:50,976 --> 01:03:53,968
The relationship between a father and a daughter
is special.

951
01:03:54,136 --> 01:03:59,256
After Veera was born
Teemu has now and then said -

952
01:03:59,416 --> 01:04:01,407
that maybe we could have
another girl.

953
01:04:01,576 --> 01:04:03,532
I have put a stop to it.

954
01:04:03,696 --> 01:04:06,164
He can beg all he wants -

955
01:04:06,336 --> 01:04:07,928
but there will be no more kids.

956
01:04:08,656 --> 01:04:12,251
Ever since he was a little boy,
, Teemu has woken up like a little bird.

957
01:04:12,416 --> 01:04:15,408
He was never grumpy.
Veera is the same.

958
01:04:16,576 --> 01:04:20,854
For many athletes
sport is their own thing -

959
01:04:21,016 --> 01:04:22,927
and their families suffer.

960
01:04:23,096 --> 01:04:27,328
But in this family, it is
a lifestyle for everyone.

961
01:04:30,536 --> 01:04:32,094
He is my idol.

962
01:04:32,656 --> 01:04:35,170
Naturally he's my dad too.

963
01:04:35,496 --> 01:04:40,524
He has always been there for
me, when nobody else is.

964
01:04:42,696 --> 01:04:44,573
How was the game?
- Okay.

965
01:04:44,736 --> 01:04:50,811
My dad plays in the NHL
and is doing something he loves.

966
01:04:51,616 --> 01:04:54,335
But it isn't necessarily
a real job.

967
01:04:57,936 --> 01:05:00,211
He always stops here.

968
01:05:00,936 --> 01:05:04,326
If there is even one person here,
, he writes an autograph.

969
01:05:07,016 --> 01:05:09,484
I never tell anybody
 who my father is.

970
01:05:09,776 --> 01:05:15,646
I don't want to be recognized
because I'm Teemu Selanne's son.

971
01:05:17,736 --> 01:05:20,887
Top athletes are selfish.

972
01:05:21,096 --> 01:05:23,769
They wouldn't be as good
if they were not.

973
01:05:23,936 --> 01:05:27,008
They do what they want to
and when they want to do it.

974
01:05:29,656 --> 01:05:31,214
Oh, they're swimming.

975
01:05:33,696 --> 01:05:38,406
It doesn't matter which one is the
top athlete in a relationship -

976
01:05:38,576 --> 01:05:42,171
the partner must understand what he or she needs.

977
01:05:42,416 --> 01:05:44,213
Otherwise things won't work.

978
01:05:44,976 --> 01:05:49,015
Teemu is the boss here.
I am his slave.

979
01:05:49,696 --> 01:05:52,688
He's making a sandwich in the kitchen.

