01:21:16,376 --> 01:21:19,925
that if I can't do them
I'll lose a part of me.

1222
01:21:30,376 --> 01:21:33,573
If I had had to quit after
the year in Colorado -

1223
01:21:33,736 --> 01:21:37,046
I would probably be a little bitter.

1224
01:21:37,496 --> 01:21:39,566
I was a free agent again.

1225
01:21:39,736 --> 01:21:42,887
I was considering
my options, staying in San Jose -

1226
01:21:43,136 --> 01:21:47,254
or moving to
a new address.

1227
01:21:48,016 --> 01:21:52,373
Paul Kariya phoned me.
His contract had also ended.

1228
01:21:52,696 --> 01:21:56,530
He had some quarrel
with Anaheim -

1229
01:21:56,856 --> 01:21:59,768
and he definitely wanted
to leave Ducks.

1230
01:22:00,096 --> 01:22:02,087
We ended up in Colorado.

1231
01:22:02,336 --> 01:22:05,248
Joe Sakic and Peter Forsberg
were there.

1232
01:22:05,496 --> 01:22:07,373
Rob Blake and the rest of the gang.

1233
01:22:07,936 --> 01:22:09,927
Expectations were sky-high.

1234
01:22:10,496 --> 01:22:13,249
People congratulated us for
getting the Cup in advance.

1235
01:22:13,656 --> 01:22:16,489
Paul and Teemu found themselves -

1236
01:22:16,656 --> 01:22:18,248
unrestricted.

1237
01:22:18,416 --> 01:22:20,691
It will be a long year.
- Yes.

1238
01:22:20,896 --> 01:22:23,729
Two players came here together.

1239
01:22:23,896 --> 01:22:27,252
When the initiative did not come from the team -

1240
01:22:27,456 --> 01:22:32,052
some people didn't like the idea.

1241
01:22:32,216 --> 01:22:37,006
They had barely welcomed us
-

1242
01:22:37,176 --> 01:22:40,532
when they reminded us of
that we had not won anything yet.

1243
01:22:43,816 --> 01:22:45,534
Things started fine.

1244
01:22:45,696 --> 01:22:48,529
We played five games really well.

1245
01:22:48,696 --> 01:22:50,891
Then Paul got a wrist fracture.

1246
01:22:51,416 --> 01:22:53,611
He was gone for four months.

1247
01:22:53,856 --> 01:22:56,973
Then something happened with the coach.

1248
01:22:57,336 --> 01:23:00,248
Although we never quarreled  -

1249
01:23:00,416 --> 01:23:03,567
I was placed on the third line.

1250
01:23:05,016 --> 01:23:07,291
I wondered what was going on.

1251
01:23:07,536 --> 01:23:10,334
Sometimes I played
on the fourth line.

1252
01:23:10,496 --> 01:23:16,014
Sometimes I played great
and was the 1st star of the night -

1253
01:23:17,096 --> 01:23:19,246
even though I was  on the third line.

1254
01:23:19,416 --> 01:23:22,408
At the next training
I ended up on the fourth line.

1255
01:23:22,576 --> 01:23:24,373
Around Christmas Sakic said-

1256
01:23:24,536 --> 01:23:28,290
it was incredible and that
he would have left already.

1257
01:23:28,736 --> 01:23:34,015
Teemu called me
after an away game and said,

1258
01:23:34,336 --> 01:23:37,692
"My knee is in such shape
that if I were a race horse -

1259
01:23:37,856 --> 01:23:39,653
I would be sausages already."

1260
01:23:40,496 --> 01:23:44,535
That was my only
bad season.

1261
01:23:45,296 --> 01:23:49,494
Media had not had the chance
to write something negative -

1262
01:23:49,896 --> 01:23:52,694
about my career or my game before it.

1263
01:23:53,536 --> 01:23:56,608
A journalist wrote
I'm like cancer -

1264
01:23:56,776 --> 01:23:59,609
causing
bad atmosphere in the team.

1265
01:23:59,776 --> 01:24:01,971
I wrote a
comment in the newspaper -

1266
01:24:02,136 --> 01:24:04,286
that after the NHL season -

1267
01:24:04,456 --> 01:24:06,890
first time
during Teemu's career -

1268
01:24:07,096 --> 01:24:11,328
it's not certain if he would be chosen
to the World Championships team.

1269
01:24:11,536 --> 01:24:14,209
I listed Colorado's problems.

1270
01:24:14,376 --> 01:24:17,209
I had a source on the inside.

1271
01:24:17,376 --> 01:24:19,253
Teemu denies everything even today.

1272
01:24:19,416 --> 01:24:22,806
If they're printing the truth
then it's okay.

1273
01:24:24,416 --> 01:24:26,691
You must live with it.

1274
01:24:27,056 --> 01:24:30,287
Joe Sakic and Peter Forsberg
sitting on a bus -

1275
01:24:30,456 --> 01:24:32,253
heading to the airport.

1276
01:24:32,416 --> 01:24:34,976
Teemu,
who had played eight minutes -

1277
01:24:35,136 --> 01:24:38,446
delayed the whole team.
Such trifles.

1278
01:24:38,656 --> 01:24:42,808
I have never understood
why people go so overboard.

1279
01:24:43,296 --> 01:24:44,775
He was pissed.

1280
01:24:44,936 --> 01:24:48,246
I did not know that such a
nice man could be so angry.

1281
01:24:48,416 --> 01:24:50,850
But he had the balls
enough to talk to me.

1282
01:24:51,016 --> 01:24:53,052
I told straight up what I thought.

1283
01:24:53,616 --> 01:24:57,450
We met at SM-liiga's gala,
in the toilet.

1284
01:24:57,816 --> 01:25:01,365
I had forgotten the whole thing,
but Teemu hadn't.

1285
01:25:01,976 --> 01:25:07,004
Later he apologized.

1286
01:25:07,176 --> 01:25:11,135
He said it was
one of his biggest mistakes.

1287
01:25:11,696 --> 01:25:15,405
I accepted his apology.

1288
01:25:15,576 --> 01:25:17,487
If you piss off a star -

1289
01:25:17,656 --> 01:25:20,295
you don't get
even the nice stories.

1290
01:25:20,456 --> 01:25:24,131
There is a song about
not wanting to replace a single day.

1291
01:25:24,296 --> 01:25:26,571
I wanted to replace
the whole year.

1292
01:25:26,776 --> 01:25:29,734
<i> Will Mattias Norstrom get a penalty? </ i>

1293
01:25:29,896 --> 01:25:31,648
<i> Or will it be Selanne? </ i>

1294
01:25:32,216 --> 01:25:34,366
<i> Selanne, for interference. </ I>

1295
01:25:36,376 --> 01:25:38,367
<i> Incredible! </ i>

1296
01:25:39,656 --> 01:25:48,371
The WC in Finland in 2003 was probably
the hardest tournament for Teemu.

1297
01:25:49,016 --> 01:25:54,409
I have never played in another game
that turned around so fast.

1298
01:25:54,616 --> 01:25:57,005
<i> Niinimaa's pass in front
of the net! </ i>

1299
01:25:57,176 --> 01:26:00,213
I have never
experienced anything similar.

1300
01:26:01,056 --> 01:26:02,774
It felt like a...

1301
01:26:02,936 --> 01:26:07,691
... Earthquake,
the entire arena rocked.

1302
01:26:08,056 --> 01:26:09,489
We were leading 5 to 1.

1303
01:26:09,696 --> 01:26:12,335
Then something happened.
I don't know what.

1304
01:26:12,496 --> 01:26:16,250
<i> Norstrom shoots. </ I>
<i> Does it bounce in? Yes, it does! </ I>

1305
01:26:16,416 --> 01:26:22,332
It felt like you could hear
if someone whispered on the top row.

1306
01:26:22,816 --> 01:26:28,846
The fans panicked
when it was 5 to 4.

1307
01:26:29,056 --> 01:26:30,774
The crowd went silent.

1308
01:26:31,896 --> 01:26:36,651
Some players simply gave up.

1309
01:26:37,296 --> 01:26:41,050
Sweden were lucky as usual.

1310
01:26:41,296 --> 01:26:44,811
<i> He sails completely freely around the goal. </ I>

1311
01:26:45,976 --> 01:26:48,365
<i> Incredible! </ I>

1312
01:26:48,576 --> 01:26:50,089
It became 6 to 5.

1313
01:26:50,336 --> 01:26:54,124
Then we were goners.
It was horrible.

1314
01:26:58,176 --> 01:27:04,126
<i> Sweden win </ i>
<i> after an incredible game. </ I>

1315
01:27:04,496 --> 01:27:06,885
<i> Finns on the bench look pale. </ I>

1316
01:27:07,056 --> 01:27:08,648
When the game was over -

1317
01:27:08,816 --> 01:27:11,728
I was out of the arena
in two minutes.

1318
01:27:11,936 --> 01:27:15,246
<i> Selanne scored the 5th goal for Finland. </ I>

1319
01:27:15,976 --> 01:27:19,013
Is it never Teemu's time to win?

1320
01:27:23,656 --> 01:27:29,367
SELÄNNE AND KURRI'S AGENT
DON BAIZLEY HAS DIED

1321
01:27:29,776 --> 01:27:33,655
I met Don during Christmas
and at the beginning of the season -

1322
01:27:33,816 --> 01:27:35,932
and he seemed to be well.

1323
01:27:36,096 --> 01:27:38,405
He was positive as always.

1324
01:27:38,616 --> 01:27:42,450
He didn't want
the doctors to tell -

1325
01:27:42,616 --> 01:27:44,891
what kind of chances he had.

1326
01:27:45,056 --> 01:27:47,695
He ​​would fight as long as he could.

1327
01:27:47,896 --> 01:27:50,046
He was a caring man.

1328
01:27:50,216 --> 01:27:52,013
He was never greedy.

1329
01:27:52,416 --> 01:27:57,649
He knew me fairly well
even before I played in the NHL.

1330
01:27:58,176 --> 01:28:02,010
When I started getting salary
he always said:

1331
01:28:02,256 --> 01:28:06,090
"Save the money. Don't buy the cars."

1332
01:28:06,256 --> 01:28:09,931
When I bought a car
I kept it a secret.

1333
01:28:10,736 --> 01:28:13,170
If he had asked
I would had confessed.

1334
01:28:16,176 --> 01:28:20,488
His positive attitude
and joy were unbelievable.

1335
01:28:20,776 --> 01:28:24,371
He was an example to us all.

1336
01:28:40,056 --> 01:28:43,685
The World Cup was played
before the lockout.

1337
01:28:43,896 --> 01:28:50,210
I didn't want to play there, because
I couldn't play at my own level.

1338
01:28:50,376 --> 01:28:52,287
But it was nice.

1339
01:28:52,456 --> 01:28:55,050
We got silver
and came close to winning.

1340
01:28:55,216 --> 01:28:58,970
After the World Cup I had a knee operation
and I decided -

1341
01:28:59,256 --> 01:29:05,013
that if the knee won't be as good
as it was at its best -

1342
01:29:05,176 --> 01:29:07,167
I won't play a single game.

1343
01:29:07,416 --> 01:29:12,854
Don Baizley said that
Teemu's career was at stake.

1344
01:29:13,016 --> 01:29:17,214
There was talk in the teams -

1345
01:29:17,376 --> 01:29:20,015
that he can't play
in the NHL anymore.

1346
01:29:20,176 --> 01:29:24,613
It was a challenge
as we so nicely say nowadays.

1347
01:29:24,776 --> 01:29:29,691
An injury is the worst way
to end a sporting career.

1348
01:29:29,856 --> 01:29:32,245
Both menisci were torn.

1349
01:29:32,416 --> 01:29:38,366
The knees were very badly  worn.

1350
01:29:39,136 --> 01:29:44,369
The patella was in wrong position.

1351
01:29:45,536 --> 01:29:50,769
We had to a complete renovation.
A year of rehabilitation.

1352
01:29:50,936 --> 01:29:54,645
Ismo, my surgeon,
gave my knee two years.

1353
01:29:54,856 --> 01:29:57,689
He said I could play
for two more years.

1354
01:29:58,016 --> 01:30:03,295
That was eight years ago.

1355
01:30:03,496 --> 01:30:08,365
The surgery gave me
in some ways a new career.

1356
01:30:08,536 --> 01:30:13,530
Has the knee been stiff?
- A little.

1357
01:30:14,896 --> 01:30:16,568
This will sting a bit.

1358
01:30:16,736 --> 01:30:18,931
Is Ismo the only one
giving you these shots?

1359
01:30:19,096 --> 01:30:20,688
Team doctors also do it.

1360
01:30:20,856 --> 01:30:24,644
It took 1 1/2 years before
the knee worked painlessly.

1361
01:30:24,816 --> 01:30:26,454
That happened one day.

1362
01:30:26,616 --> 01:30:29,892
It was incredible.
I did not hurt anywhere.

1363
01:30:30,056 --> 01:30:33,446
I knew that everything would be fine.

1364
01:30:34,216 --> 01:30:38,255
My agent phoned Brian Burke, who
was the general manager at the time -

1365
01:30:38,416 --> 01:30:41,806
and said Teemu
wants to come back to Anaheim.

1366
01:30:41,976 --> 01:30:44,012
He asked if it was possible.

1367
01:30:44,976 --> 01:30:47,888
Burke said the team can't afford me.

1368
01:30:48,056 --> 01:30:51,253
A few weeks later
Brian called up Don -

1369
01:30:51,536 --> 01:30:53,811
and said that they have some money now.

1370
01:30:55,216 --> 01:30:57,730
I signed on real cheap.

1371
01:30:58,456 --> 01:31:00,606
I said immediately that I will sign.

1372
01:31:00,776 --> 01:31:04,655
It was fun to get back
with the fans and everything.

1373
01:31:04,816 --> 01:31:06,693
I was also healthy.

1374
01:31:07,096 --> 01:31:09,610
I felt as good
as during my first year.

1375
01:31:09,776 --> 01:31:12,051
In the conference finals -

1376
01:31:12,216 --> 01:31:15,686
We played against Edmonton
and lost the series 4 to 1.

1377
01:31:15,856 --> 01:31:17,847
We got better all the time.

1378
01:31:18,016 --> 01:31:22,089
It showed how good a
team we could become.

1379
01:31:22,256 --> 01:31:23,974
After the last match -

1380
01:31:24,136 --> 01:31:26,650
I said to the guys:
"Next year, remember -

1381
01:31:26,816 --> 01:31:28,647
how disappointed we were."

1382
01:31:29,376 --> 01:31:32,527
We could go even further.

1383
01:31:37,656 --> 01:31:40,011
Brian Burke said to me:

1384
01:31:41,816 --> 01:31:45,331
"I know exactly what you're worth."

1385
01:31:45,896 --> 01:31:51,971
He ​​promised me that if I took this salary -

1386
01:31:52,656 --> 01:31:56,535
he would use
the difference -

1387
01:31:56,696 --> 01:32:01,565
about three million dollars -

1388
01:32:01,776 --> 01:32:08,329
to acquire a player who could
help us win the Stanley Cup.

1389
01:32:09,216 --> 01:32:12,367
I remember it well.
It was my birthday.

1390
01:32:12,576 --> 01:32:17,331
I got a call.
They had acquired Chris Pronger.

1391
01:32:17,856 --> 01:32:22,691
Too bad no one filmed me.
My smile was quite wide.

1392
01:32:22,856 --> 01:32:27,452
I knew he was the missing link
we didn't have last year.

1393
01:32:27,736 --> 01:32:29,374
After the Stanley Cup Finals -

1394
01:32:29,616 --> 01:32:32,335
I was invited
to Anaheim's dressing room.

1395
01:32:32,496 --> 01:32:36,045
Older players, like
Scott Niedermayer, were on their way out -

1396
01:32:36,216 --> 01:32:38,252
in suits.

1397
01:32:38,456 --> 01:32:41,448
Teemu had all the equipment
and tied skates -

1398
01:32:41,616 --> 01:32:43,527
2 1/2 hours after the game.

1399
01:32:43,696 --> 01:32:46,494
It was the only year
we had started well.

1400
01:32:46,656 --> 01:32:50,285
We hadn't lost a game
after 17 or 18 games.

1401
01:32:50,536 --> 01:32:53,687
It was a good start.

1402
01:32:53,936 --> 01:32:56,575
Play offs are fun for us players.

1403
01:32:56,816 --> 01:32:59,569
Each shift,
each hit -

1404
01:32:59,736 --> 01:33:02,773
and each time you
throw yourself in front of the puck...

1405
01:33:02,976 --> 01:33:06,446
Everything affects everything.
Little things decide the outcome.

1406
01:33:31,416 --> 01:33:33,327
During the Finals -

1407
01:33:34,056 --> 01:33:37,605
we had 12 guys queuing
up for the doctor.

1408
01:33:37,896 --> 01:33:44,165
We got Toradol injections that remove
almost any pain whatsoever.

1409
01:33:44,456 --> 01:33:48,051
Without it, I think none of us
could have played.

1410
01:34:25,536 --> 01:34:27,174
An incredible feeling.

1411
01:34:27,336 --> 01:34:30,772
I've been waiting for
to win something big for 15 years.

1412
01:34:33,176 --> 01:34:36,407
Sometimes I thought
that this would never happen.

1413
01:34:36,576 --> 01:34:38,294
That's why this is so important.

1414
01:34:38,456 --> 01:34:42,415
I have been close to winning the Olympic gold,
the World Championships the World Cup -

1415
01:34:44,576 --> 01:34:46,089
but it hasn't happened.

1416
01:34:46,256 --> 01:34:49,726
Now I have won the biggest trophy
a hockey player can win.

1417
01:34:50,976 --> 01:34:54,013
I always wanted to quit on top.

1418
01:34:54,336 --> 01:34:57,567
Stanley Cup crowns my career.

1419
01:34:57,816 --> 01:35:00,011
I think I've earned this finale.

1420
01:35:16,576 --> 01:35:19,693
SUMMER 2007, FlNLAND

1421
01:35:35,736 --> 01:35:37,135
Hi.

1422
01:35:43,536 --> 01:35:45,492
Is this for me?
- Yes.

1423
01:35:45,656 --> 01:35:48,124
And this also.
- Thanks!

1424
01:35:48,776 --> 01:35:50,926
Veeti wrote "Anaheim".

1425
01:35:53,896 --> 01:35:55,295
It's pretty big, isn't it?

1426
01:35:55,456 --> 01:35:59,927
How has your summer been?
- Pretty bad.

1427
01:36:00,096 --> 01:36:02,291
Yeah, the weather has also been bad.

1428
01:36:02,496 --> 01:36:06,045
Teemu sent this picture
after his rookie season in Winnipeg.

1429
01:36:06,216 --> 01:36:08,446
I have it on the wall at home.

1430
01:36:08,816 --> 01:36:11,808
If you look at this picture -

1431
01:36:11,976 --> 01:36:17,528
that was 2007 -

1432
01:36:18,496 --> 01:36:22,011
a lot has happened
between taking these.

1433
01:36:22,216 --> 01:36:26,334
I'll always treasure them.

1434
01:36:26,856 --> 01:36:30,974
These will hang on my wall
as long as I live.

1435
01:36:37,096 --> 01:36:38,893
When I won the Stanley Cup -

1436
01:36:39,056 --> 01:36:42,571
I was totally sure
that my career was over.

1437
01:36:42,736 --> 01:36:45,296
There is no better way to end
-

1438
01:36:45,456 --> 01:36:47,287
than a championship -

1439
01:36:47,536 --> 01:36:50,175
especially
a Stanley Cup championship.

1440
01:36:50,336 --> 01:36:53,931
I didn't think
I'd find the motivation -

1441
01:36:54,096 --> 01:36:58,055
to work hard
and torture myself every Friday -

1442
01:36:58,216 --> 01:37:01,094
by running
in the forests of Hila.

1443
01:37:01,456 --> 01:37:04,766
I had achieved
what I had dreamed and fantasized about -

1444
01:37:04,936 --> 01:37:06,767
since I was a small boy.

1445
01:37:07,616 --> 01:37:10,972
I didn't think I could
find the motivation for a comeback.

1446
01:37:11,136 --> 01:37:13,047
I thought
I had done my share.

1447
01:37:13,216 --> 01:37:15,776
We returned to Anaheim
after the summer.

1448
01:37:15,976 --> 01:37:20,174
I was a normal family man
and drove the boys to training.

1449
01:37:20,336 --> 01:37:22,486
I played golf during the days.

1450
01:37:23,896 --> 01:37:27,411
Until the boys wanted to go and watch hockey.

1451
01:37:27,976 --> 01:37:29,932
We went to a couple of games.

1452
01:37:30,096 --> 01:37:34,248
I looked around and thought:
"That guy missed that chance."

1453
01:37:34,416 --> 01:37:36,054
"I would have scored."

1454
01:37:36,216 --> 01:37:41,973
Scott Niedermayer, who also
was about to end his career -

1455
01:37:42,816 --> 01:37:45,694
called and asked if I wanted to skate.

1456
01:37:45,856 --> 01:37:48,290
I didn't even know
where my equipment was.

1457
01:37:48,456 --> 01:37:50,651
I didn't know
where I had that stuff.

1458
01:37:51,336 --> 01:37:53,327
I said I could come.

1459
01:37:53,536 --> 01:37:55,925
I would see if it was still fun.

1460
01:37:58,576 --> 01:38:01,409
I went
and thought it was stupid.

1461
01:38:01,736 --> 01:38:03,408
"I quit."

1462
01:38:04,136 --> 01:38:10,211
A few weeks later
an old teammate called -

1463
01:38:10,376 --> 01:38:12,844
and asked if I would like
play for fun.

1464
01:38:13,176 --> 01:38:15,485
A beer league game.

1465
01:38:15,656 --> 01:38:18,648
We would play
and drink a few beers afterwards.

1466
01:38:18,816 --> 01:38:20,534
I said, "Sure!"

1467
01:38:20,696 --> 01:38:23,893
All of a sudden, it was great fun.

1468
01:38:24,696 --> 01:38:30,487
I thought about it for a while
and spoke with my family.

1469
01:38:31,536 --> 01:38:36,052
Then I decided
to play again.

1470
01:38:36,296 --> 01:38:40,767
I've been thinking about the
highlight of Teemu's career.

1471
01:38:41,296 --> 01:38:43,685
I want to have a broader perspective.

1472
01:38:43,856 --> 01:38:45,687
It's not the 76 goals.

1473
01:38:46,056 --> 01:38:47,728
Not his natural talent.

1474
01:38:47,896 --> 01:38:50,330
Not that he is such nice and happy guy.

1475
01:38:50,496 --> 01:38:53,886
We are speaking about
incredibly tough top-level sports.

1476
01:38:54,056 --> 01:38:56,854
I think the biggest
thing is that he -

1477
01:38:57,096 --> 01:39:00,247
after getting
all the money in the world -

1478
01:39:00,576 --> 01:39:02,806
and after all the prizes -

1479
01:39:03,096 --> 01:39:04,973
even after the Stanley Cup -

1480
01:39:05,136 --> 01:39:07,127
and all he got from the sport -

1481
01:39:07,296 --> 01:39:10,572
aged 36 or 37 -

1482
01:39:10,896 --> 01:39:15,208
decides to do
a new proper attempt to win.

1483
01:39:16,376 --> 01:39:17,889
Now!

1484
01:39:19,456 --> 01:39:20,855
Now!

1485
01:39:22,536 --> 01:39:23,935
One more time!

1486
01:39:24,096 --> 01:39:25,734
When you see the X-ray picture -

1487
01:39:25,896 --> 01:39:29,252
it's hard to believe he has played
with that knee in a long time.

1488
01:39:30,176 --> 01:39:35,933
When you have to train the same things
in a new way -

1489
01:39:36,376 --> 01:39:40,085
training will be diverse as it needs to.

1490
01:39:40,376 --> 01:39:42,571
If you can't run
you can cycle.

1491
01:39:46,576 --> 01:39:48,373
I want to play in the NHL.

1492
01:39:48,536 --> 01:39:51,733
I have to focus on
that I will, too.

1493
01:39:53,496 --> 01:39:56,727
When I train with Teemu
I notice -

1494
01:39:56,976 --> 01:40:00,446
how much it requires
to get to that level -

1495
01:40:00,976 --> 01:40:03,410
, and how he also trains
during summers.

1496
01:40:05,496 --> 01:40:09,569
My Friday workout
when I torture myself -

1497
01:40:09,736 --> 01:40:13,524
is the only workout
I don't like.

1498
01:40:13,696 --> 01:40:18,372
But sometimes you have to
stretch your limits.

1499
01:40:21,416 --> 01:40:23,805
It's amazing how good
 a shape he's in.

1500
01:40:23,976 --> 01:40:28,891
And he doesn't get winded
and bend over on his stick.

1501
01:40:29,056 --> 01:40:32,492
At his age he's the best
athlete in the world.

1502
01:40:32,656 --> 01:40:38,208
He's playing at 42 20 minutes a night
against the best players in the world+.

1503
01:40:38,376 --> 01:40:42,733
A big lifestyle change
and new training methods.

1504
01:40:42,936 --> 01:40:46,451
He made an incredible comeback
straight to the top.

1505
01:40:46,976 --> 01:40:51,970
An older player must lose weight.
You have to get your weight down.

1506
01:40:52,136 --> 01:40:56,527
I've noticed he's slowly letting his weight get
lower so he can be as fast as he was.

1507
01:40:56,696 --> 01:41:00,291
Only now Teemu has
found his limits.

1508
01:41:00,616 --> 01:41:05,007
The most difficult thing in sports
is finding your maximum potential.

1509
01:41:05,216 --> 01:41:07,013
Teemu has done that now.

1510
01:41:07,256 --> 01:41:14,253
That's why I admire him
ten times more now than ever before.

1511
01:41:23,776 --> 01:41:29,214
The evolution stops when one is
satisfied. That thought has brought me here.

1512
01:41:33,456 --> 01:41:36,766
It's been a long time since I was
playing here last time.

1513
01:41:36,936 --> 01:41:39,655
This is something special.

1514
01:41:39,816 --> 01:41:46,415
This city and people here have been
supporting me all these 20 years.

1515
01:41:47,136 --> 01:41:49,969
That's why this is so special for me.

1516
01:41:50,136 --> 01:41:53,845
Too bad We are here for only one day.

1517
01:42:04,736 --> 01:42:06,772
TEEMU WE FORGIVE YOU. COME HOME.

1518
01:42:07,856 --> 01:42:09,653
<i> Tonight we are saluting him

1519
01:42:09,816 --> 01:42:15,732
<i> for his amazing career </ i>
<i> and his unquivering passion for our city. </ I>

1520
01:42:26,856 --> 01:42:30,451
Teemu got to have an emotional farewell
15 years late.

1521
01:42:38,656 --> 01:42:42,171
I am only one of millions of dads -

1522
01:42:42,376 --> 01:42:45,573
who have taken their boys
to training and games.

1523
01:42:46,096 --> 01:42:49,611
Teemu wouldn't be
an elite hockey player -

1524
01:42:49,936 --> 01:42:51,733
without dad.

1525
01:42:52,256 --> 01:42:59,207
This necklace has everything
that is important in my life.

1526
01:42:59,456 --> 01:43:05,133
A hockey club, of course.
A golf club.

1527
01:43:05,776 --> 01:43:09,132
The heart symbolizes love of course.

1528
01:43:09,376 --> 01:43:11,970
A four-leaf clover -

1529
01:43:12,256 --> 01:43:19,685
and a cross I got when I
was confirmed as a 15-year-old.

1530
01:43:20,336 --> 01:43:24,807
I've weared the cross
ever since.

1531
01:43:28,656 --> 01:43:31,853
When previously asked about
what's most important in life -

1532
01:43:32,016 --> 01:43:34,484
he always answered being healthy.

1533
01:43:35,416 --> 01:43:39,125
But after he began visiting
Children's Hospital -

1534
01:43:39,296 --> 01:43:43,130
and saw how happy
little patients could be -

1535
01:43:43,296 --> 01:43:46,971
he has started to say that the
main thing is to be happy.

1536
01:43:55,607 --> 01:43:57,006
When the crew first asked -

1537
01:43:57,087 --> 01:43:58,884
if they could make a movie about me
I replied, "Absolutely not."

1538
01:43:58,967 --> 01:44:00,366
But later I changed my mind.

1539
01:44:00,447 --> 01:44:02,244
I wanted to make a film that can
inspire people to believe -

1540
01:44:02,327 --> 01:44:03,885
dreams can be fulfilled
through hard work.

1541
01:44:03,967 --> 01:44:05,480
Now I also want to thank all the people
-

1542
01:44:05,567 --> 01:44:07,080
who made my dream possible.
Teemu Selanne.

